raw_text = "~ wake_up
Tux: Psst... Nova... wake up.
Tux: You nodded off in Operating Systems class.
Tux: Good timing, though. We can practice inside Linuxia.
Tux: I am Tux, your guide.
Tux: First check: can you move with WASD?
=> END

~ movement_success
Tux: Nice. Movement online.
Tux: Great. You are in control now.
Tux: Next, walk up to the glowing marker and press E to interact.
=> END

~ interact_prompt
Tux: Interact is how you talk to people and use objects.
Tux: Get close to the marker, then press E.
=> END

~ interact_success
Tux: Perfect. Interaction works.
=> END

~ hud_unlock
Tux: Time to unlock your HUD.
Tux: Think of the bottom bar as your Linux taskbar.
Tux: The icons there are system apps.
Tux: TUX app = hints and your current goal.
Tux: TERMINAL app = command line practice.
Tux: To open the skill shop, open TERMINAL and type: shop.
=> END

~ terminal_objective
Tux: Terminal check. Open TERMINAL and run these commands:
Tux: 1) pwd
Tux: 2) ls
Tux: 3) cat <file-name>  (example: cat onboarding_notes.txt)
Tux: Quick meanings: pwd = where you are, ls = what is here, cat = read a file.
Tux: I will wait here until all three are done.
=> END

~ terminal_complete
Tux: Nice work.
Tux: You now know the 3 basics: where you are, what is here, and how to read files.
=> END

~ linuxia_ready
Tux: Final question, Nova. Ready to enter Linuxia?
- What is Linuxia?
	=> linuxia_explain
- I am ready. Let's go.
	=> linuxia_yes
- Not yet, give me one more minute.
	=> linuxia_no

~ linuxia_explain
Tux: Linuxia is the live system beyond this safe zone.
Tux: Every command has consequences there.
Tux: Read output first, then choose your next command.
- Okay. I am ready.
	=> linuxia_yes
- I still need a moment.
	=> linuxia_no

~ linuxia_yes
Tux: Good. Confidence plus care. That is how real admins grow.
=> END

~ linuxia_no
Tux: Fair. A careful operator beats a reckless hero.
Tux: Ping me from the TUX panel when you are ready.
=> END

~ linuxia_arrival_intro
Tux: Welcome to Linuxia proper, Nova. I am with you from here on.
Tux: Think of me as your helper while you learn this system and its people.
Tux: Before charging into deeper zones, talk to the NPCs in this hamlet first.
Tux: Each NPC teaches one OS lesson and a few useful commands.
Tux: Ask questions, read carefully, and we will move step by step.
=> END
"
metadata/dialogue_manager_version = "3.9.0"
